timeline.bodyText:
@dkayiwa since I saw your name on the commiters of this file and the ModuleActivatorTest. Can you describe to us what these are testing?
The reason why I am asking is that for the JUnit 4 to 5 migration we need to figure out for each of these test helpers if they are only used internally within openmrs-core. This one is used in ModuleActivatorTest in org.openmrs.module and WebModuleActivatorTest in `package org.openmrs.web.test;.
If it is only used internally we can choose to switch to JUnit 5 without also providing a JUnit 4 version. If it is for example used by module devs we need to provide a JUnit 4 version so they have a transition period. So they can choose to migrate at their own pace.
@achilep I will wait for @dkayiwa before we make a decision on what to do with this test helper.
